    {
        "content": "<p>If you'd rather have a monadicity theorem of the form \"a functor is monadic iff it is right adjoint and creates certain colimits\", rather than one in terms of the 2-Yoneda embedding, it should be possible to derive one from the formal monadicity theorem in <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.10405\">Relative monadicity</a>.</p>",
        "id": 400787556,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathanael Arkor",
        "timestamp": 1699378685
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I was asking if my statement follows from 8.1; and yes, I'd like to have something like the second statement...</p>",
